usage() {
    cat <<'EOF'
puppet-trace — unified puppet process monitor/tracer

Subcommands:
  puppet-trace enable               install postrun_command hook
  puppet-trace disable              remove postrun_command hook
  puppet-trace once [OPTIONS]       one-shot trace run with full monitoring
  puppet-trace status               show enabled/disabled state and last report path
  puppet-trace collect              internal — called by puppet as postrun_command
  puppet-trace report [OUTDIR]      regenerate HTML from existing artifact dir
  puppet-trace ship OUTDIR REMOTE   rsync artifacts + regenerate report on remote
  puppet-trace demo [--outdir DIR] [--flamegraph SVG]  generate a demo report with mock data (no puppet/root required)
  puppet-trace diff DIR1 DIR2 [--out FILE] [--html]    diff two run outdirs
    REMOTE = [user@]host:/path
    --include-strace  also ship strace.raw (large; needed for remote re-correlation)

Once-mode options:
  --dry-run                    Skip actual puppet run; generate report from fixture data
  --follow                     Stream puppet.log lines + I/O stats while puppet runs
  --outdir DIR                 Override output directory (default: /var/log/puppet-trace/<timestamp>/)
  --prometheus-textfile FILE   Write Prometheus textfile metrics to FILE after run
  --push-server HOST:PORT      Push report files to puppet-trace-server after run
  --enable-profiling HOST:PORT Enable puppetserver profiling before run, disable after
  -- ARGS                      Pass remaining args to puppet agent

Examples:
  sudo puppet-trace once
  puppet-trace report /var/log/puppet-trace/20260523-163231
  puppet-trace ship /var/log/puppet-trace/20260523-163231 user@monitor.example.com:/data/traces/forge/
  sudo puppet-trace enable

Output: <outdir>/report.html (self-contained HTML, no external deps)
Ship workflow: agent runs puppet-trace once → ship to reporting server → open HTML
EOF
    exit 0
}

